In addition to that, obviously there is, sort of, ongoing inflationary pressure, we insulate ourselves to some degree based on our forward-buying program and that has actually helped us clearly this year. There'll be a bit more pressure in the back half, but at the same time, as you know, we tend to take pricing after Labor Day in both of our businesses. And I think you would expect to see that pattern continue. So is there some somewhat more inflation out there? There is. Are we going to be pricing to deal with it? We certainly are the investments in our brands and the investments that we've made in supplying our customers, I think is what enables us to take that pricing as we have every year.

